            <h3>File System Layout</h3>
            <ul>
            <li>/public - Where the Audio Catalog html file will be created.</li>
            <li>/public/media - default location where you will place all your media files and edit descriptors. </li>
            <li>/public/templates - Template text files to describe each media file and catalog descriptor files.</li>
            <li>/docs - Documentation help files. Instructions.</li>
            <li>/src - TypeScript source files only for developers use only.</li>
            <li>/views - ejs template engine used by developers to generate html and display it as well as create it. Mostly developers only.</li>
            <li>readme.md - Read Me file displayed in GitHub for this repository.</li>
            <li>/out - Actual server javascript files generated by TypeScript. This is the server and should not be modified.</li>
            <li>Files or folders not described are developer only type files and should not be modified unless you know what you are doing.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Once server is running it is by default <em></em>http://localhost:5000/docs</p>em>, unless you changed this value. So here is a link for your convenience. <a href="http://localhost:5000/docs/index.html">Launch browser to documentation Overview</a>a> if server is running.</a>"" </p>
            <p>Command for quick reference start server: $<h5>npm run start</h5></p>
