            <div class="col-sm-6 col-lg-9 border" role="main" title="main">
            <h1>Download and Setup</>
            
            <h4><a href="<%= repo %> ">Download the Audio Catalog Generator Repository</a></h4> 
            <p>Click the link above and select the download you want. You may need to create a longin account in order to download the repo. There are 2 most popular ways to download a repo. The easist and most convenient is the http methodhowever this requires git to be installed and you may not have it. The 2nd method is zip file.</p>
              <p><em>Http</em> this method is the most convenient way to download repos that you do not plan on modifying and uploading. You will need to install the git system if it is not already installed. Linux and WSL have git preinstalled. <em>Notes for Blind users</em> if installing Git for Windows, do not let it install into wsl/linux nor do you want the gui.</p>
            <h5>GitHub Screen Reader Instructions</h5>
            <ul>
            <li>Go to the Repo.</li>
            <li>Press "r" repeatedly until you hear "Repository Region"</li>
            <li>Press "b" for button, until you hear either code button not expanded" or "copy button". If on code button, press to expand and cursor down until you hear you option.</li>
            <li>If http then until you copy button, otherwise until you hear download.
            <li>Http method press "copy button", then navigate to a folder from you command prompt or linux terminal.</li>
            <li>Http: At the prompt gype $git clone (Paste here) then press enter
            <li>Http: Audio Catalog folder will be created. rename if desired to whatever name you want. 
            <li>Http: You have now downloaded and are ready for installing and running.</li>
            <li>Download Zip Method Your zip file should have been downloaded to you download folder when you selected earlier. You can try this direct <a href="<%= zip %> ">link to the zip file</a>a></a>.</li>
            <li>Download: Launch you Windows Explorer and open the zip file in your download folder.</li>
            <li>Download: Download: Enter into you zip file into the inner "Audio Catalog" folder. Now copy that folder <ctrl>+ "c". Paste it into the location you want it placed such as "c:\catalogs". </li>
            <li> Download: You will now have an Audio Catalog folder. You will need to navigate to it via a command prompt or terminal prompt depending on where you put it.</li>
            </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 border bg-dark text-white mt-0 mx-3" role="region"  title="Setup & Run Generator33">
                <h2>SetUp and Run Generator</h2>
                <p><em>Requires NodeJS</em> installed. Download and install <a href="<%= nodejs %> " >here</a>. Pick your operating system and version. Latest version is fine. </p>
                <h3>Installation Setup</h3> 
                <p>Navigate to the folder A"Audio Catalog" from your command prompt using terminal or windows run command (cmd.exe) depending on where you created the folder. Now type: <em>$npm install</em> . You will see a whole lot of stuff go by, it will finish momentarilly. It is downloading and installing the server components.</p>
                <p>Once finished you can type <em>$npm run start</em> to bring up the server. When it starts up it will report that it is listening on port 5000, unless you changed it using advanced options.</p>
                <p>Now open your browser and enter <em>http://localhost:5000/docs</em> these instructions should come up . Congratulations the generator is now installed and running. </p>
                <p>Next time you only ned to type <em>npm run start</em> </p>
                <p>Now you can begin defining/importing/generating HTML. </p>
                
